Task 7: Online Fonts and Favicon

- Online Fonts: Fonts hosted on external servers that can be integrated into a website using CSS.
- Google Fonts: A popular service for accessing a wide range of fonts.
- Favicon: A small image used to represent a website in browser tabs and bookmarks.
Example:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Online Fonts and Favicon</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto">
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="favicon.ico">
</head>
<body> Â  

    <h1>Heading</h1>
    <p>This text is using the Roboto font.</p>
</body>
</html>